const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What retrieval mechanism does Perplexity AI use?',
    a: 'Perplexity uses retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) for all queries. When a user submits a prompt, Perplexity first retrieves a set of candidate web pages using its own index (built by PerplexityBot), then passes that retrieved content to a large language model as context to generate the final answer. Every cited source in a Perplexity response is a page that was retrieved and used as grounding context — not a result of a fixed training snapshot.',
