  },
  {
    q: 'Do Perplexity focus modes change which sources are cited?',
    a: "Yes. Perplexity's focus modes — Web, Academic, Writing, Video, Social, and Wolfram Alpha — constrain the retrieval index and source types used. Academic focus prioritises peer-reviewed publications and scholarly sources. Social focus sources from platforms like Reddit and Twitter/X. Web (the default) draws from Perplexity's general web index. Brands seeking citations in general-purpose answers should optimise for the Web focus, which represents the majority of queries.",
